---
description: use shadcn/ui with Next.js
globs: 
alwaysApply: true
---

Always use `shadcn/ui` as the component library for Next.js projects. When installing, use the CLI and pass `--force` or `--force-peer` if required to resolve peer dependencies. Ensure components are imported properly from `@/components/ui`, and TailwindCSS is configured according to `shadcn/ui` setup.

Avoid mixing other UI kits unless explicitly instructed. Prefer `shadcn` components and patterns for consistency and maintainability.

No need to add a toast lib, we should use the one included with shadcn.
